review_blob: A true India Pale Ale. High in gravity and loaded with hops. We add Cascade hops straight into the fermentor creating a full citrus nose and lasting aftertaste. This crisp brew is perfect for those warm days of summer.......  that is exactly what i was thinking
I enjoyed the mississippi mud.  I was a little skeptical trying it, but It was a surprise.  Tastes good and has a nice bottle.
Another disappointment.  But I agree with Davehgbrew A bitter pale ale that isnt that tasty. Decent aftertaste, but I wouldnt get it again.

Ive been waiting to try Ipswitch Original Ale for a long time, when I finally got it, I was very disappointed.  Maybe my expectations were too high.  But when I look in my refridgerator to get a beer, I defently would pick a bud light over it.
Cheap, is all I can say about this beer.  Also there is a frenchman that I know that considers this one of his top beers.
It is a great local beer, has good flavor.  Starting to find more and more Sam Adams type beers that I am enjoying.
Not worth the $$.  It was good at most, and not worth the price.
first sip sucked.  Got better, but overall very disappointing for Buzzards Bay

not the greatest beer, but not the worst beer.  It is different.  As davhgbrew says Cloudy yellowish appearence, with a nice lacey white head. Unfiltered wheat, and can actually see particles floating in it. Has nice flavor with bit of a bitter aftertaste. Nice beer.

Had this beer when I toured the brewery, this beer was my familys favorite. I thought it wasnt bad for a gettin drunk brew, too bad we only get regular Moosehead in the states. This beer is definitely better than some of the mass produced bottles of water we have(Coors light, Miller, etc.)

Smells skunky, tastes bitter, clean and refreshing. I wouldnt drink more than one or two of them, but I like the bottle and its the only Italian beer I know. I like to have one while eating zupa di pesch at Amicis.
Tastes like every U.S full flavored beer. Dont go out of your way!
Way too much hops for my liking, even for an I.P.A. , still a good beer, but definitely the breweries worst beer.
Wasnt undelicious, tasted like a domestic Ive had before, was very drinkable, good solid beer from a great brewery!

As the ad says, No it wasnt Thomas Edison, but it was actually Joe Owades who invented the light beer.  A pretty bold statement. It is a full flavored light beer, and possibly one of the best American style light beers Ive ever had. It has a fruity aroma and a nice lacey head. Good full flavor but a peculiar aftertaste. A very drinkable light beer.

When I first smelled this beer I recognized pancakes I used to get at I-hop with blueberry syrup, and then I made the connection of the name! Overwhelmingly blueberry flavor, but not to the point of making you sick. Nice drinkable beer, but couldnt have more than 3 of them.
Always enjoy amstel.  It is the beer drinkers, light beer.

There are two images I have for Bud, 1. I feel a sense of pride in the all-American beer and figure Bud isnt half bad for the price 2. I think of every person I know that drinks Bud on a regular basis,and that image gets tarnished. Overall it may be watered down, flavorless cheap trailor beer, but Its American,its good with Pizza, and thats all we ask of it!
Goes very well with sushi, one of my favorites.
Favoriate beer of the frenchman in the thanksgiving club, maybe very good on tap, but just another watered down American style macro canned.
Good for Sam Adams.  Similar to other winter brews.  Nice sweet flavor, not overwhelming.  Spices are apparent, cannot figure out some of them..  but tastes good.
nice dark color, a head that dissapates quickly, nice aroma and not too overwhelming spices, overall great pale ale.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Organic / Old Brewery Pale Ale

review_blob: Nice deep color, the spices were very apparent, tasted a lot of cinnamon among other spices. A little to fruity flavored for my liking, but an overall good beer.
Not bad for a n/a, but why is right?
This beer confirms the fact that everything from Pabst is awful. I think they purposefully brew shitty beer.

nothing special, had it off tap at the brewery and it was good because it was all you can drink in the half hour tour of the bar, probably wouldnt go out of my way to drink any of the Moosehead products.
When I had this beer it was from the brewer in New Brunswick, maybe it was that it was fresh or they gave the tours their best batches, but I think this beer was pretty good.
Burst of grain flavor with the first sip, that is a bit overwhelming, but starts to grow on you. Average amber

The label says 8.1% alcohol, it doesnt do it justice. This stuff hits you like a brick, have two and you can feel the night slipping away. This stuff is brutal,in taste and what does to you. I will never go out of my way to drink one again.

Has a thinner body compared to the draught, although still has the classic guinness head and a great bitter aftertaste. Overall better than draught in a bottle!Earlier Rating: 1/14/2002 Total Score: 2.9Draught is much better, this is more of a normal beer then a guinness.  When I think of guinness i imagine more thicker then this.  It is good, but nothing special
Nothing special, As said in other ratings of this beer.  nothing outstanding and nothing bad.  It is alright.
I did Not think it was as bad as the ratings give it.
Perfect drinkers beer, very nice for the winter
This shit is bad, not as bad as pabst or the beast, but its pretty danm close. Of all the 40s this is definitely the worst. I think the company actually wants it to taste bad.
Mickeys 40s was one of the first beers I was introduced to. Its cheap, good tasting, and it got you plowed, need I say more!
I like it a lot, but some of the other members of the club think it tastes like cough syrup.  I guess you either like it, or hate it.
Good commercials on TV, disappointed at first, but then after drinking it a couple times it is not too bad.  maybe it is an aquired taste.

First time trying their seasonal beer so my opinion is subjective. Definitely has an earthy taste to it, the spices are very apparent. Has a terrific head and a great smooth texture, bit of a spicy bite and a bitter aftertaste. Really good winter beer, but thats about it.
beer_name: Anchor Our Special Ale (2001 and earlier)

review_blob: The name blond is deceiving, has a very full bodied flavor. Nice head on the pour and an impressive aftertaste. Very good beer!

Personally I have been impressed with the widget, and it works well with this beer. Has a very smooth creamy flavor, with a mixture of sweet and bitter aftertastes. This is a really good drinking beer, but only for a few because its thick.
I know it got me drunk, besides that, I dont remember it being a great beer.
This beer is for Germans!
Has a hoppy aroma with a bit of an aftertaste. Not a bad beer, but not great!
beer_name: Florida Beer Key West Sunset Ale

review_blob: tasted very similar to Becks, an overpriced, bitter, flavorless beer.
The only thing I remember about this beer is the red label with the indian on it and that the beer wasnt that bad!
This beer had a very funky taste, and it didnt get better as I drank more unlike some low quality beers. Overall this is not a very good beer!
Id rather drink a west African stable boys piss, this beer is one of the worst ive ever come across!
Very smooth drinkable substitute for a bass/guiness at a bar, also very economical. Overall solid choice.
Suprising flavor for a cheap American lager, some say its better than bud light!

Suprisingly wonderful beer. We bought a twelve pack for 7$, well worth the money and some. The beer has a terrific oak and honey flavor with a hint of honey and a great aftertaste that leaves you wanting more. Great economical find!
